The paper presents an interactive visualization system for exploring and understanding neural networks, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The system uses activation distributions to summarize what a model has learned, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses comparing activation distributions across classes and instances, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
